- name="install-system76-power" \
  dialog-name="Power Management" \
  short-description="Install Power Management" \
  long-description="""
Install System76 Power Management: Provides full power profile support (Performance, Balanced, Power Saver) via the standard D-Bus interface used by XFCE, COSMIC, Waybar and other desktop environments.

It is a complete drop-in replacement for power-profiles-daemon and is the default choice in Ditana for maximum consistency across all supported desktops (including their parallel installation). The package also adds hardware-specific optimisations such as NVIDIA hybrid graphics switching where applicable.
""" \
  spdx-identifiers="GPL-3.0-or-later" \
  default-value="`install-desktop-environment AND has-battery AND NOT virtual-environment`" {
    arch-packages "system76-power"
  }
- name="prevent-suspend-environment" \
  dialog-name="Power Management" \
  short-description="Disable suspend and hibernation" \
  long-description="""
This setting is intended to be used only in virtual environments (VirtualBox, KVM, VMware, etc.). It disables suspend, sleep, hibernate and hybrid-sleep targets, because these are typically unreliable or non-functional inside virtual machines.

Masking them prevents hangs, black screens or data corruption when running under a hypervisor.
""" \
  spdx-identifiers="" \
  default-value="`virtual-environment`" {
    chroot-script "`systemctl mask suspend.target sleep.target hibernate.target hybrid-sleep.target`"
  }
